Package craj

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CircleCalculationResultTable
    Holds the calculation result data and provides methods to get the maximum value, a visualization of the data, and the circle findings regarding the given reference circle values.
    CircleCrossCalculator
    This class is used to calculate the count and the sum of intensity of circles drawn around every pixel in an given edges image.
    CircleFinding
    This class holds the data of a circle finding.
    ContrastEnhancer
    This class provides methods to enhance the contrast of an image using the specified lower bound percentage and upper bound percentage.
    EdgeDetector
    This class provides methods to detect the edges using a given Sobel-operator.
    EdgeDetector.EdgeDetectorParameter
    This class holds the parameter data for the EdgeDetector
    Histogram
    Creates a histogram for the given image-data
    PerfectCircleCoordinates
    Represents the pixel data of a perfect circle which is used to draw circles in the resulting cross count and cross value tables and increase the performance because the calculation of the circle pixels in its origin space is already done and does not have to be calculated every time a circle is drawn.
    PerfectCircleCoordinates.DifferenceFromOrigin
    This class holds the difference of the x and y coordinates of pixel data regarding its given origin.
    ReferenceCircle
    Represents the perfect circle which holds the maximum cross value and cross count a circle with the same diameter could possibly have.
    ReferenceCircle.ReferenceCircleParameters
    This class holds the parameter data for the ReferenceCircle
    SobelMatrix
    This class generates a Sobel-matrix with the given size automatically.
